{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a dog traceability system to run alongside Livestock Services",
        "additional_details": "Microchips do not prove ownership, which we think makes theft & abuse easy. An estimated 36,965 dogs were handled as strays in 2023-24.\r\nA DEFRA register would create birth-to-death records to:\r\nHelp police & wardens trace a dog\u2019s life quicker and more easily.\r\nReduce \u00a325m/year in police kennel costs (2024/25 estimate).\r\nEstablish legal ownership, reduce abuse and abandonment.\r\nClose loopholes for illegal breeding and exports.",
        "background": "We call on the UK Government to introduce a mandatory DEFRA-run National Dog Register, alongside the Livestock Information Service; to record every dog from birth & track all changes of owner, sale, rehoming, import, export & death, replacing the current fragmented microchip system.",
